6 640 675 682 911 991 \u591c3 \u591c6}}\n|2.036\n|20.104\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n|{{BJS stations|Qingnianlu}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u9752\u5e74\u8def}}}}\n|\n|{{small|75 126 419 451 468 494 499 553 605 675 682 911 991 \u591c3 \u591c6 \u591c13 \u4e13141}}\n|1.282\n|21.386\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Dalianpo}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u8921\u88e2\u5761}}}}\n|\n|{{small|499 517 675 911}}\n|3.999\n|25.385\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Huangqu}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u9ec4\u6e20}}}}\n|\n|{{small|499 517 583 675 911}}\n|1.238\n|26.623\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Changying}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u5e38\u8425}}}}\n|\n|{{small|488 586 587 639 675 911 \u4e1339}}\n|1.854\n|28.477\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Caofang}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u8349\u623f}}}}\n|\n|{{small|306 488 499 517 587 639 675 819 824 911 \u4e1339}}\n|1.405\n|29.882\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Wuzixueyuanlu}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u7269\u8d44\u5b66\u9662\u8def}}}}\n|\n|{{small|435 587 675 813 824 911}}\n|2.115\n|31.997\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[Tongzhou District, Beijing|Tongzhou]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Tongzhou Beiguan}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u901a\u5dde\u5317\u5173}}}}\n|\n|{{small|316 342 435 582 587 911 924 \u4e1364 \u4e1377 \u4e1388}}\n|2.557\n|34.554\n|- bgcolor=\"lightgrey\"\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|''{{BJS stations|Tongyunmen}}''\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u901a\u8fd0\u95e8}}}}\n|\n|\n|1.468\n|36.022\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Beiyunhe West}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u5317\u8fd0\u6cb3\u897f}}}}\n|\n|{{small|317 552 809}}\n|1.543\n|37.565\n|- \n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\uff5c\n|{{BJS stations|Beiyunhe East}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u5317\u8fd0\u6cb3\u4e1c}}}}\n|\n|{{small|312 442 \u591c29}}\n|1.599\n|39.164\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n|{{BJS stations|Haojiafu}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u90dd\u5bb6\u5e9c}}}}\n|\n|{{small|312 442 \u591c29 \u4e13203 \u4e13205 \u4e13206}}\n|0.929\n|40.093\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n|{{BJS stations|Dongxiayuan}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u4e1c\u590f\u56ed}}}}\n|\n|{{small|312 442 804 822 893 894 \u591c29 \u4e13203 \u4e13205 \u4e13206}}\n|1.346\n|41.439\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n| align=\"center\" |\u25cf\n|{{BJS stations|Lucheng}}\n|{{large|{{lang|zh-cn|\u6f5e\u57ce}}}}\n|\n|{{small|312 442 822 893 894 \u591c29 \u4e13203 \u4e13205}}\n|1.194\n|42.633\n|- style=\"background:#{{BJS color|6}}; height: 2pt\"\n| colspan=\"9\" |\n|}<br />\n==Planning==\n\nLine 6 was originally planned to be an east\u2013west line passing under Chaoyang Avenue continuing straight westward. However, this alignment would make the central section of Line 6 tunnel extremely close to the [[Forbidden City]]. Issues of historic conservation and protection were raised against the proposed alignment. To avoid damaging cultural relics in the area, the entire western and middle section of line 6 was shifted {{convert|1.5|km|abbr=on}} northward to [[Ping'an Avenue]], forming the route of Line 6 today.<ref>{{cite video|url=http://tv.cntv.cn/video/C38730/20121003100798_CN25|title=Archived copy|publisher=[[China Central Television]]|time=07:20|accessdate=2012-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130101074033/http://tv.cntv.cn/video/C38730/20121003100798_CN25|archive-date=2013-01-01|script-title=zh:\u300a\u8d85\u7ea7\u5de5\u7a0b\u300b\u7b2c\u4e09\u96c6\u300a\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c1\u7f51\u7edc\u300b|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caslkx.ac.cn/onews.asp?id=660|script-title=zh:2012\u5e74\u4e5d\u6708\u4efd\u79d1\u666e\u8bba\u575b\u62a5\u544a\u4f1a|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140913080448/http://www.caslkx.ac.cn/onews.asp?id=660|archivedate=2014-09-13|accessdate=2012-12-29}}</ref> Line 6 started construction on December 8, 2007 as one of the \"horizontal\" east-west lines of the \"three-ring, four horizontal and five vertical and seven radial\" Beijing Subway masterplan.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/newscenter/2007-12/08/content_7218646.htm|date=2007-12-08|accessdate=2012-12-29|script-title=zh:\u5317\u4eac5\u6761\u65b0\u5730\u94c112\u67088\u65e5\u540c\u65f6\u5f00\u5de5\u5efa\u8bbe}}</ref> Construction is planned in three phases, the first phase in central Beijing, followed by extensions into the eastern and western suburbs. \n\nLine 6 was projected to have a short term volume of 700,000 passengers per day and a long term daily passenger traffic of 1.4 million passengers. Though due to its alignment through some of Beijing's densest residential neighborhoods and paralleling the overcapacity and busy [[Line 1, Beijing Subway|Line 1]], some industry leaders believed that the average daily passenger flow of the line may reach 1.4 million passengers per day sooner than expected.<ref name=\"opening 2012\" /> Within the first few months of operation, weekday ridership was at 320,000 passengers. However, by 2014, daily ridership had risen to 700,000 with sections operating at 100% capacity during rush hour. Authorities responded by adding more trains and shortening headway to reduce crowding on the line.<ref name=\"weekday avg\" />\n\n===Phase I===\n[[File:Flashlight map of BJS Line 6, 2013-10-29.jpg|thumb|right|Route map of Line 6 Phase I]]\nIn Phase I, Line 6 runs {{convert|30|km|abbr=on}} from Haidian Wuluju in [[Haidian District]] to Caofang in [[Chaoyang District, Beijing|Chaoyang District]] following Linglong Road, Sanlihe Road, Chaoyang North Road, the west bank of the [[Grand Canal (China)|Grand Canal]], and Yunhe East Road. In Phase I, there were 20 stations except the reserved [[Erligou station]]. Construction began in December 2007 and was completed in 2012.  Total investment for Phase I was estimated at [[Renminbi|\u00a5]]19.7 billion.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" />\n\nLine 6 in Phase I was originally slated to have elevated tracks for {{convert|7|km|abbr=on}}, east of the [[5th Ring Road]], from Dingfuzhuang and Changying. After residents along the route raised concerns about train noise, planners reconsidered and ultimately decided to keep all of Phase I underground.<ref>[http://news.zhulong.com/dongtai/read79594.htm \u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u53ef\u80fd\u566a\u97f3\u6270\u6c11 \u6709\u671b\u6539\u8d70\u5730\u4e0b ->(\u884c\u4e1a\u52a8\u6001)->\u884c\u4e1a\u52a8\u6001->\u7b51\u9f99\u7f51<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://house.news.qingnet.cn/200801/2792332.htm \u5317\u4eac\u5e02\u89c4\u5212\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a\u5173\u4e8e\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u9ad8\u67b6\u7ebf\u7684\u590d\u51fd - \u623f\u4ea7 - \u9752\u4f20\u5a92<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707050657/http://house.news.qingnet.cn/200801/2792332.htm|date=2011-07-07}}</ref><ref>[http://society.people.com.cn/GB/56023/56026/8166313.html \"\u5317\u4eac\u5e02\u89c4\u5212\u59d4\u56de\u590d\u4eba\u6c11\u70ed\u7ebf\uff1a\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u4e00\u671f\u5de5\u7a0b\u5747\u4e3a\u5730\u4e0b\u7ebf\" ''\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51''] October 13, 2008</ref> This made the first phase of Line 6 completely underground.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjghw.gov.cn/web/static/articles/catalog_14300/article_ff808081262b02de01262c2fa1a90005/ff808081262b02de01262c2fa1a90005.html|title=Archived copy|date=2010-01-14|publisher=\u5317\u4eac\u5e02\u89c4\u5212\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|script-title=zh:\u8f68\u9053\u4ea4\u901a6\u53f7\u7ebf\u4e00\u671f\u5de5\u7a0b\u89c4\u5212\u65b9\u6848\u516c\u544a|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101227055616/http://www.bjghw.gov.cn/web/static/articles/catalog_14300/article_ff808081262b02de01262c2fa1a90005/ff808081262b02de01262c2fa1a90005.html|archive-date=2010-12-27|accessdate=2012-12-29}}</ref>\n\n===Phase II (eastern extension) ===\n[[File:Flashlight map of Line 6, Beijing Subway Phase II.jpg|thumb|right|Route map of Line 6 Phase II]]\nIn Phase II, which opened in 2014, Line 6 was extended further east by about {{convert|12|km|abbr=on}} through seven stations from {{BJS stations|Caofang}} to {{BJS stations|Lucheng}} in Tongzhou New Town. Like Phase I, the Phase II track is entirely underground. \n\nThe extension was designed to have express and local services using passing tracks at select stations.<ref>http://society.people.com.cn/n/2013/1113/c1008-23531866.html</ref> However, due to a shortage of rolling stock, express services have yet to be implemented when the Phase II opens in 2014. In 2018, the government announced that sufficient rolling stock had arrived to begin implementing an express service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bj.people.com.cn/n2/2018/0302/c82840-31300298.html|date=2018-03-02|website=bj.people.com.cn|script-title=zh:\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u5c06\u4e3a\u526f\u4e2d\u5fc3\u8dd1\u201c\u5927\u7ad9\u5feb\u8f66\u201d}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinanews.com/cj/2018/03-02/8458424.shtml|last=chinanews|website=www.chinanews.com|script-title=zh:\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u897f\u5ef6\u62df\u5e74\u5e95\u901a\u8f66 \u6216\u5c06\u201c\u5927\u7ad9\u8dd1\u5feb\u8f66\u201d-\u4e2d\u65b0\u7f51|access-date=2018-03-04}}</ref> Express services started operating on March 31, 2020.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n===Phase III (western extension) ===\nLine 6 was originally planned to terminate at [[Cishousi Station]] with the [[S1 line (Beijing Subway)|S1 Line]] continuing the line westward. In 2011, because of issues of low capacity and electromagnetic radiation concerns of Maglev technology, city planning authorities proposed to detach several stations from the [[S1 Line, Beijing Subway|S1 line]]. This would extend Line 6 10.556-km west with six stations from Jin'anqiao to Haidian Wuluju (the western terminus of Phase I).<ref>{{in lang|zh}}[http://news.sina.com.cn/c/2011-04-03/134022233240.shtml \u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u897f\u5ef6\u6bb5\u653e\u5f03\u91c7\u7528\u78c1\u60ac\u6d6e\u5f62\u5f0f] July 2, 2011</ref><ref name=\"autogenerated10\">(Chinese)[http://beijing.qianlong.com/3825/2012/03/12/6405@7769581.htm \"\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u5c06\u897f\u5ef6\u81f3\u6768\u5e84\u4e1c\u8857\"] 2012-03-23</ref><ref name=\"sina201810\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.cn/2018-10-18/detail-ihmhafis3343083.d.html|title=\u4e24\u6761\u5730\u94c1\u7ebf\u8def\u5e74\u5185\u5c06\"\u5347\u7ea7\"|date=2018-10-18}}</ref> All stations are below ground.<ref name=\"rails\">{{cite web|url=http://home.rails.com.cn/news.php?id=41153|title=Archived copy|date=2013-11-21|publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u94c1\u9053\u79d1\u5b66\u7814\u7a76\u9662|script-title=zh:\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u897f\u5ef6\u5de5\u7a0b\u53d8\u66f4\u516c\u793a|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221194647/http://home.rails.com.cn/news.php?id=41153|archive-date=2013-12-21|accessdate=2013-11-21}}</ref> This replaced the S1 Line section between Cishousi and [[Pingguoyuan Station|Pingguoyuan]] station.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://beijing.qianlong.com/3825/2011/04/27/2821@6929625.htm|title=Archived copy|date=2011-04-27|accessdate=2012-12-29|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111214090630/http://beijing.qianlong.com/3825/2011/04/27/2821%406929625.htm|archive-date=2011-12-14|script-title=zh:8\u53f7\u7ebf3\u671f6\u53f7\u7ebf\u897f\u5ef6\u5c06\u5f00\u5de5 2015\u5e74\u603b\u91cc\u7a0b666\u516c\u91cc}}</ref> Later the plan was revised with Line 6 being further extended westward beyond Pingguoyuan to Jin'anqiao station, paralleling the S1 Line.<ref name=\"rails\" /> The revision was formalized and submitted to the [[National Development and Reform Commission]] for review in March 2012.<ref name=\"rails\" /> \n\n==History==\n* As of October 2007, Line 6 was planned to feature both express and local stations, but those plans have not been incorporated into the construction of Phase I.<ref>{{cite web |language=zh-hans |url=http://news.tom.com/2007-10-30/0020/09005486.html |script-title=zh:\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u94c16\u53f7\u7ebf\u65b9\u6848\u83b7\u6279\u590d \u5c06\u5c1d\u8bd5\u5927\u7ad9\u5feb\u8f66(\u56fe)_TOM\u65b0\u95fb |date=2007-10-30 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-07-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071102152310/http://news.tom.com/2007-10-30/0020/09005486.html |archive-date=2007-11-02 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* On March 22, 2010, the tunneling work on Line 6 commenced near Shilipu in Chaoyang District.<ref>{{cite web |language=zh-hans |url=http://news.163.com/10/0323/02/62E6G7O3000146BB.html |script-title=zh:6\u53f7\u7ebf\u4e00\u671f\u5f00\u59cb\u201c\u6316\u5730\u9053\u201d |date=2010-03-23 |website=[[163.com]] news}}</ref>\n* As of November 2010, plans for Phase II contained distinct express and local stations.<ref>(Chinese) [http://news.cntv.cn/20101118/106073.shtml 2010-11-18]</ref>\n* On December 30, 2012, the Phase I stations opened, except for Erligou.\n* On December 28, 2014, the Phase II stations opened, except for Tongyunmen and Beiyunhe East.\n* On December 30, 2018, the Phase III stations, except for Pingguoyuan, were opened. An infill station on Phase II, Beiyunhe East station, was also opened.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-align: right;\"\n!Segment!!Commencement!!Length!!Station(s)!!Name\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Haidian Wuluju \u2014 Caofang\n| 30 December 2012\n| {{convert|29.882|km|mi|2|abbr=on}}\n| 20\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Phase 1\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Caofang \u2014 Lucheng\n| 28 December 2014\n| {{convert|12.751|km|mi|2|abbr=on}}\n| 6\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Phase 2\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Beiyunhe East\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 30 December 2018\n| infill station\n| 1\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Jin'anqiao \u2014 Haidian Wuluju\n| {{convert|10.556|km|mi|2|abbr=on}}<ref name=sina201810>{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.cn/2018-10-18/detail-ihmhafis3343083.d.html|title=\u4e24\u6761\u5730\u94c1\u7ebf\u8def\u5e74\u5185\u5c06\"\u5347\u7ea7\"|date=2018-10-18}}</ref>\n| 5\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"| Phase 3\n|}\n==Rolling Stock==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-align: center;\"\n!Model!!Image!!Manufacturer!!Year Built!!Year Refurbished!!Amount in Service!!Fleet Numbers!!Depot\n|-\n| [[:ja:\u5317\u4eac\u5730\u4e0b\u9244DKZ47\u578b\u96fb\u8eca|DKZ47]]\n| [[File:Inside_train_of_Beijing_Subway_Line_6_20181124.jpg|150px]]\n| [[CRRC Changchun Railway Vehicles]]\n| 2011\n| Never\n| 84\n| 06 001-06 084\n| [[:zh:\u4e94\u8def\u505c\u8f66\u573a|Wulu]]<br/>[[:zh:\u4e94\u91cc\u6865\u8f66\u8f86\u6bb5|Wuliqiao]]<br/>Dongxiaoying\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Commonscat-inline|Line 6, Beijing Subway}}\n\n{{Beijing transit}}\n{{Beijing Subway}}\n\n[[Category:Beijing Subway lines]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in China]]\n", "name_user": "Terramorphous", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line_6_(Beijing_Subway)"}
